task.summary: Default task
Initial commit of working code.
Added some rudimentary 3D rotation to the board.
Better 3D + modularization of 3D rotation into its own directive.
General refactoring.
Removed custom patched versions of jquery and lodash. Too many other libraries depend on the global variables. :-(
Cleaned up directive dependencies a bit.
Completely refactored the treemap and treemap-tile code, ready for arbitrary layout algorithms.
Switched to a 'need-to-know' interface for the layout engine, which now has access only to 'importance' and 'reposition'.
Made the layout engine independent from tile spacing.
Cleaned up the module and Angular service architecture; got rid of some potentially confusing conventions.
Cleaned up the module and Angular service architecture. Got rid of some potentially confusing conventions. Now auto-generating log message for each module loaded by RequireJS.
Arbitrary tiling with nested tiling layouts. Controls for full-sizing a tile.
Proper icon buttons for maximizing treemap tiles.
Now able to populate the treemap with the actual data from the FMA. But the code has become rather messy now. It's time for some refactoring.
Partway through implementing the connection graph on top of the treemap.
Tried to make d3 graphs on top of the circuitboard work. No luck so far.
Fixed inactive-tile glyph.
Finally fixed the strange bug that kept the inner vascular junctions from showing up properly.
Updated all npm and bower packages to their latest version.

Re-enabled tile animation + not loading any connections when connections are not turned on. The previous version used 'ng-show'. This version uses 'ng-if'. This makes the app faster when connections are off.
Fixed the bug where opening a tile would sometimes show weird behavior.
Some refactoring: added $.fn.addSvgClass, $.fn.removeSvgClass and $.fn.toggleSvgClass. Also removed useless jquery extension $.fn.equals.
Rudimentary controls and output for simulation.
Changed the simulation traces to stretch the entire width of the graph area, as per Bernard's request.
Minor changes.
Proper stream support in the simulation-panel. Also, the panel is now properly animated into view.
Fixed position of slider bubble at maximum.
Since tiles no longer have overflow: hidden, tile are now being explicitly hidden when they should be invisible.
Improved $bind service. It now accepts a thisArg and no longer returns a string (an old convention).
Fixed and improved 3D rotation code.
Fixed and improved 3D rotation code.
Set up a catch for an error that sometimes appears.
Gave 3D model button an icon. Still have to selectively show it only for tiles that have 3D models.
Variable glyphs on the circuitboard, linked to the simulation panel.
Renamed app parameter in all modules.
Showing descendant counters.
Showing extra information about protein expression, including IDs and small molecule interaction count in the sidebar.
Showing even more complete protein information, including hyperlinks to external resources.
Fix to hide (currently irrelevant) inconsistency in the database.
Removed outdated database dump.
Fixed stupid error.
First commit in a big refactoring branch, redoing the circuitboard, focus system, etc.
Some fixes, such as: weight: Infinity now works with the new version.
Integrated 8 new static 3D brain models.
Fixed active / inactive tile management.
Implemented stand-alone trace-diagram directive, tested it, but have not yet integrated it, nor enabled shadow traces in it.
Added heart models converted from Zinc. I don't think they work properly. They look like they're only half there.
Fixed interaction between maximization and (1) tiles with no siblings and (2) highlighting.
Fixed interaction between maximization and (1) tiles with no siblings and (2) highlighting.
Adapted the top- and side-bars w.r.t. branding and control information.
Implemented right-click-to-close.
Introduced the amy-circuit-board directive.
Made a start on modular d3.
The hasty changes made to see vascular segment data in the left side-panel.
Removed files that belong in the refactoring branch.
Added Typescript classes for the Artefact concept.
Removed some old commented code.
Fixed protein focus event.
Progress on the protein details panel.
Just some minor stuff, moving lines around, removing debugging output, etc.
Properly showing meta-info about vascular junctions and segments in the left side-panel. Hover gives focus; click fixes focus.
Full meta-data in the left side-panel for both vascular and neural connections and junctions. Also fixed some bugs and improved some aesthetics.
Fixed a mistake where focus-fixed edges would not be colored green.
Protein interactions are now an artefact and can have information in the side-panel.
Implemented search for literal entity IDs in the search box.
Implemented full text search of the reachable entity database.
Edge-artifacts now show two links in the side-panel that refix focus to their respective end-points. Also showing more info for protein endpoints of a PPI.
Added back 3D manipulation of the circuitboard in a more modular way. Actual 3D models cannot yet be displayed.
Added back the feature to show static 3D models.
Some small refinements in 3D model toggling.
Great refactoring of the artefact class hierarchy, and used it to simplify the graph-related code and remove duplicate code.
Small fix to highlight the tile in which a protein-interaction edge has focus.
Fixed and simplified some things in the artefact hierarchy.
Wrote some minimal beginning code for encapsulating static 3D models in an artefact. This probably breaks the build at this point. To be continued tomorrow.
Reworked the focus-broadcast system into the Artefact class hierarchy.
Details and 3D models of protein domains.
Better small molecule interaction 'revealer'. Now using the HTML5 semantic tags <details> and <summary>.
Removing pagination from the small molecule interaction view in cases where the number of interactions is smaller than the page-size.
Refactored the directory structure and the way scss files are compiled.
Put the 'tile-map' service and directive in their own module. They are relatively self-contained, and could be released as an independent library at some point.
Added the trace-diagram module to the project, with the new ability to pass shadow traces in from outside.
A number of changes, including new time controls, and some fixes to scss code.
Upgraded several libraries and set proper version dependencies in bower.json.
Fixed a typo in bower.json.
Updated to latest angular-slider version and re-applied the local patch fixing the 'low bubble' bug: https://github.com/Venturocket/angular-slider/pull/47
A great deal of changes here, including a systematic way to manage Typescript header files in tsd, and a modular way to call up floating trace diagrams and couple them with the timing module.
Created a new way to generate a range of equidistant colors, and used it for the categorization of protein domains and variable glyphs.
Minor refactoring.
Updated AngularJS and fixed our own code to compensate with a change.
Added the five linked 3D FTU models.
Unfinished additions to static 3D models. Mostly, it's about displaying models consisting of multiple OBJ files.
Unfinished additions to static 3D models. Mostly, it's about displaying models consisting of multiple OBJ files.
Working FTU 3D model (also added contracting heart json file).
Animated 3D heart model.
Smoother mouse-dragging on the slider bar.
Added proper jquery dependency.
Small fix.
Attempt to use AngularJS one-time binding where possible.
Trace dialog no longer has a title overlapping with the close button.
Applied the one-time binding of AngularJS 1.3 where possible, resulting in (minor) overall performance improvement.
Improved distinct color stream.
Removed old unused source files.
Locally fixed one-time binding to not deep-copy objects by patching the angular library, and using it in two places now to improve performance.
General typing update.
Some local refactorings to make code simpler.
Added some more dynamic libraries necessary (sometimes) for running the cellml tool (GMS).
Built much of the required infrastructure for consuming CellML output.
Working CellML simulations, including good UI.
Re-enabled shadow traces.
Re-added static 3D models that were missing (for some reason).
Remapped Beeler & Reuter variables to Vascular Thoracic.
Fixed the excessive repulsive charge for inner connection junctions.
Set the 3D heart model heart-rate to 72 bpm.
Fixed the bug that occurred at any cellML data-fetching delay.
Finished Navier Stokes simulation, including variable glyphs on the relevant edges.
Almost finished with Navier Stokes + associated CellML model.
Connected CellML model to Navier Stokes Simulation, and gave variable glyphs focus on hover.
Typing updates
Fix w.r.t. svg elements not liking 'right' and 'bottom' properties.
Fixed the display of trace diagrams.
Improved .gitignore structure.
Started on a Gulp file.
Typing update.
